body_html:
Hi
I have a graph with 3 inputs. For a particular application, two of the inputs are constants.
By applying the Graph Transform Tools, I want to replace those input nodes with the constant values.

Can you help with this thing? When running the graph transform with ignoring the two inputs, I get the following error:

fold_constants: Ignoring error You must feed a value for placeholder tensor 'model_1/keep_probabilty' with dtype float [[Node: model_1/keep_probabilty = Placeholder[dtype=DT_FLOAT, shape=<unknown>]()]]

body:
Hi 
I have a graph with 3 inputs. For a particular application, two of the inputs are constants. 
By applying the Graph Transform Tools, I want to replace those input nodes with the constant values. 

Can you help with this thing? When running the graph transform with ignoring the two inputs, I get the following error:

`fold_constants: Ignoring error You must feed a value for placeholder tensor 'model_1/keep_probabilty' with dtype float [[Node: model_1/keep_probabilty = Placeholder[dtype=DT_FLOAT, shape=<unknown>]()]]`
